results.name: An analog of Pascal's triangle: T(n,k) = A092143(n)/(A092143(n-k)*A092143(k)), 0 <= k <= n.
comment: It appears that the T(n,k) are always integers. This would follow from the conjectured prime factorization given in the comments section of A092143.
xref: Second column T(n, 1) is A007955, A092143.
results.author: _Peter Bala_, Apr 15 2007
